In [58]:
from scipy.optimize import curve_fit

def obj(x, tau, env, start):
    return env + (start - env) * np.e**(-x/tau)

opt_params, _ = curve_fit(obj, times, temps, p0=[100, 22, 42])
print(opt_params[0], np.sqrt(_[0][0]))
plt.scatter(times, temps, label="Data",s=1)
plt.plot(times, obj(times, *opt_params),'r-', label="Best fit curve")
plt.xlabel("Time (min)")
plt.ylabel("Temperature (deg. C)")
plt.title("Calculating time constant of cooling")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

filename = "./plots_data/variac_duty_cycle_plot_data_20240716-105109.csv"

temps = []
dcs = []

    times.append(line[0])
    temps.append(line[1])
    dcs.append(line[2])

temps = np.array(temps[0:])

temps = temps.astype(float) - 30
dcs = dcs.astype(float)

temps = []

    times.append(line[0])
    temps.append(line[1])
